PUBLIC DOMAIN DEDICATION

The compilation in this repository — including the folder structure,
filenames, metadata, the `compile_data.py` build script, and all
commentary excerpts drawn from public-domain sources (such as the
ANF/NPNF series, CCEL, and similar collections) — is released into the
public domain. You may copy, modify, distribute, and use this material
for any purpose, without restriction or attribution.

FAIR USE NOTICE

Some commentaries in this repository are limited excerpts from works
still under copyright by their authors or estates. These excerpts are
included under the fair use doctrine (17 U.S.C. § 107, and equivalents
in other jurisdictions) for nonprofit, educational, and scholarly
purposes: the excerpts are limited in length relative to the original
work, they are reorganized transformatively by Scripture passage for
study and reference, and they are not intended to substitute for the
original works.

Copyright in those excerpts remains with their original rights holders
and/or their estates. Nothing in the public-domain dedication above
transfers, waives, or limits those rights. If you are the copyright
holder of any such excerpt and would like it removed, please open an
issue on this repository.

Downstream users who redistribute this database are responsible for
their own fair-use analysis in their jurisdiction and use case. The
public-domain dedication in the first section does not extend to the
fair-use excerpts covered by this notice.
